JOHANNESBURG – Libya has issued over 200 warrants of arrest for suspected refugee smugglers. The country says the smuggling network includes African embassy officials and members of the security services. Last year, videos and pictures of the alleged underground slave trade emerged on broadcaster CNN, which sparked international condemnation. READ: SA calls for immediate end to slave trade in Libya Libya has been in political turmoil since the fall of long-time leader Muammar Gaddafi in 2011. With instability in the country, it has become a key point on the journey for thousands of Sub-Saharan African refugees trying to reach Europe. eNCA